The paper proposes a position-aided approach for efficient beam alignment in millimeter wave systems with analog beamforming, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The approach involves using a multipath fingerprint database, which is a technique used in wireless communication systems (cs.MM). The paper also discusses optimizing candidate beam selection and evaluating the proposed approach using realistic channels generated from a commercial ray-tracing simulator, which are topics related to control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
